    "( 43), at a rate which is at least O (t -1/2).Observe that the influence of the initial condition f in (A, w) is only seen in the equilibrium h ∞ (w) through the preserved initial average opinion m in w. Moreover, notice that if we consider the original model and if a p belongs to case (i), then all agents tend to become active (linearly fast, see Proposition 3) and, in this situation, the evolution of h(t, w) is again given by (42).",
    "Therefore, the marginal h(t, w) converges toward the equilibrium h ∞ (w).",
    "Obviously, an analogous situation occurs if a p belongs to case (iii), with ε appearing at the exponents of (43) instead of ω p + ε.Consider now the presence of opinion leaders and recall that (see Eq.",
    "( 19)) the evolution of the activity level depends on the quantities ω p + ω ℓ, a p + a ℓ, and 2ε, defined at the beginning of Section 3.",
    "Thanks to the results obtained in the previous Subsection 4.1, we are now able to demonstrate Conjecture 1 (i.e., the relaxation of the population's average opinion m w (t) toward the leaders' average opinion µ ℓ) under the realistic assumption that f in (A, w) has a compact support."
